8:
A-any much longer a-and my fur
might j-just freeze right off!
13: Ngh... It just doesn't make any sense!
17:
Cipher is at her studies again it
seems.
20:
What does that have to do with the
sudden drop in—
22:
Wait. You mean to say she can
somehow manipulate the weather...
with her FEELINGS?
26:
Alk, you gotta do somethin' about
this.
29:
Before we all die of frostbite out
here, if possible.
40:
It appears I'm still unable to reign in
my magic past a certain threshold.
43:
You're saying that you've become
even stronger than before?
46:
My ice powers have, at least. I can
even fabricate frozen orbs out of
thin air now.
48:
But that's it. I've basically made no
headway in actually getting it all
under control!
51:
Believe me, I've searched far and
wide for help—I even sought help
from other wizards in Palpebra.
52:
But if an expert in the frozen arcane
arts can't even master this, what
hope do they have of helping me?
59: Rei would've been able to do it.
61:
I'm hopeless... Perhaps we all
would've been better off if I was the
one who became sick instead.
65:
That is THE dumbest thing I've heard
out of her mouth yet. Geez, I wish
she'd unfreeze me right now so I can
punch the stupid out of her!
69:
Well, you know... she's just dealing
with  this in her own way.
71:
Yeah? Well, she shouldn't be saying
stuff like that in any scenario!
73:
Like, there's no way I'd be able to
save her by myself. Get real!
75:
She said that if it were you, you'd be
able to do anything.
77:
She may act dumb, but I know she's
smart. The problem is that she's a
big scaredy-cat who won't get off
her lazy butt to actually apply
herself!
81: So it seems that you need her.
91:
But whatever it is, I'm sure she's on
to something.
96:
Uh, hello? I can't see a thing out
there in this state, you know. What's
the sitch?
98:
We're on a ship. And soon we'll be
taking you to another world, by
means of the ocean.
100:
Hoo, boy... I'm getting the
heebie-jeebies.
101:
But those friends of yours are pretty
cray, huh?
107:
Heh... Ahaha! I thought the very
same... Oh Stella, you magnificent
genius!
110: What will you think of next?
114:
Resuming operation: Move-in. Is
everything under control, Cipher?
118:
Leave it to me, Stella. This amount of
ice should be a piece of cake.
122:
Damn, woman. That's some
impressive magic!
125:
We've got all the time in the world,
Cipher. I know I say a lot of stuff, but...
126:
I believe in you, Ciph. And so does
the rest of your crazy crew,
apparently.
127:
And maybe one day you'll live up to
this personality you've made for
yourself.
130: Heh... Look who's prattling on now?
133:
But of course, that goes without
saying! Hold on tight, Rei!
136:
...No, no, no! You've got the
technique all wrong!
137:
Geez, how sloppy can your magic
get? No—not like that! Did you
already forget what was on the last
page?
141:
Will you let me work in peace
already?!
143:
How am I supposed to concentrate
on this with you critiquing every
single thing I do?!
146:
Oh, brother. Here we go AGAIN with
the excuses...
149: Are they seriously at it again?
153:
Yes. But I think... they both seem
happier now.
